  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 5 flow-speed operating points, with Latin hypercube sampling over 12 uncertain input parameters. A comprehensive UQ campaign (1 200 model evaluations) informed factor-level assignments and revealed sensitivity of the hemolysis index to shear-stress threshold and time-step size. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
